						<summary>

						<p>Slab (another) paved in the <hi rend="italic">mukha maṇḍapa</hi> of the Pushpēśvara temple on the hill.</p>						

						<p>This is dated only in the cyclic year Śubhakṛit.</p>						

						<p>It refers the obeisance to the god Pushpanātha of Pushpagiri, by Basava-battuḍu, son of Pallavōli Veṁgaya. In late characters.</p>						

